  "response_text": "A young adult woman with medium-brown skin and short, dark curly hair sits facing forward in a rounded pale green armchair in a bright, softly lit home setting. She wears a coral-pink short-sleeved blouse with a gathered neckline and puffed sleeves. Behind her are light-colored walls, a white column, framed pictures, and a shelf; a small side table sits to one side. She looks toward the viewer, then lowers her gaze and brings one hand to the outside and back of her upper arm, rubbing the skin as if indicating an area of concern.\n\nThe view shifts to her arm and sleeve. Her hand glides over the upper arm near the short sleeve cuff, then wraps around and rubs downward along the arm in a slow, deliberate motion. The pale green chair remains blurred behind her arm. Next, a white open jar of cream is shown being held in someone’s hand, with blue denim visible beneath it. The label reads “Gold Bond Ultimate” and “rough & bumpy skin daily therapy cream,” with smaller text above indicating “8 intensive moisturizers.” Large gold text beside the jar says “NEW.” A fingertip presses into the smooth white cream and lifts out a small dollop, showing its thick, soft texture.\n\nThe woman’s upper arm returns to view as she applies the cream, spreading it across the outside of her arm with the flat of her hand. A small Gold Bond Ultimate logo appears at the lower right. As her hand continues smoothing the lotion over her skin, pale text appears on the right side: first “exfoliates,” then “smoothes,” then “softens,” stacked vertically in warm-toned lettering. Her arm looks slightly shiny where the cream has been rubbed in.\n\nA soft-focus image of the woman seated in the chair appears behind large centered text. The text reads, “90% saw smoother, softer skin in just 1 week,” with “90%” and “just 1 week” especially large. Tiny fine print appears underneath, citing a clinical study of rough and bumpy skin sufferers. Behind the text, the woman looks down and touches her arm, then smiles.\n\nThe view returns to her pink sleeve and upper arm as she runs her fingers over the treated area, gently pressing and stroking the skin. She then sits upright again in the pale green chair, smiling broadly at the viewer while rubbing one forearm with the opposite hand, appearing pleased with the smoothness. The commercial ends on a clean white background with the product jar centered: a white tub with a gold lid labeled “Gold Bond Ultimate rough & bumpy skin daily therapy cream.” To the left, the words “Ultimate lotion.” appear in light gold and blue text.",
